  "texts": [
    "Recall that untwisted bilayer graphene naturally realizes the Bernal (AB-stacking) configuration, implying that it is energetically more favourable than AA-stacking [127].",
    "Therefore, the AB regions in TBG expand at the expense of AA regions, while the latter also buckle out of plane slightly to locally increase the interlayer spacing.",
    "Such lattice relaxation and corrugation effects can have a dramatic effect on the moiré band structure, and become especially pronounced for smaller twist angles.",
    "For θ ≲ 0.5 •, the moiré lattice is better thought of as large AB and BA domains separated by a triangular soliton network [128][129][130][131].",
    "The out-of-plane buckling in the AA region also motivates choosing a slightly weaker interlayer tunneling amplitude w AA between sites on the same sublattice in the two layers relative to the amplitude w AB for tunneling between opposite sublattices."
  ],
